description:
Replace NSViewRepresentable dropdown with native SwiftUI Menu.

## Current
Notebar/Views/DropdownMenuView.swift - NSViewRepresentable + NSPopUpButton + Coordinator

## Target
```swift
struct DropdownMenuView: View {
    var body: some View {
        Menu {
            Button("Quit") { NSApplication.shared.terminate(nil) }
        } label: {
            Image(systemName: "gearshape")
        }
    }
}
```

Modernize to @Observable (Swift 5.9+/macOS 14+).

Note: TextManager eliminated by Ghostly-daz.

## Step 1: Explore
Search for:
- ObservableObject conformances
- @Published properties
- @ObservedObject usages in views

## Step 2: Update ThemeManager
```swift
// Before
class ThemeManager: ObservableObject {
    @Published var isThemeEditor: Bool = false
}

// After
@Observable
class ThemeManager {
    var isThemeEditor: Bool = false
}
```

## Step 3: Update views
Remove @ObservedObject, pass ThemeManager directly or use @Bindable for bindings.

Replace AppDelegate pattern with SwiftUI App lifecycle using MenuBarExtra.

## Delete
- AppDelegate.swift
- Main.storyboard

## Create: GhostlyApp.swift
```swift
import SwiftUI

@main
struct GhostlyApp: App {
    var body: some Scene {
        MenuBarExtra("Ghostly", image: "MenubarIcon") {
            ContentView()
        }
        .menuBarExtraStyle(.window)
    }
}
```

## Modify: Info.plist
Remove NSMainStoryboardFile key.
